==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diagonial
<hw>Di`a*go"ni*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Diagonal;
diametrical; hence; diametrically opposed.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sin can have no tenure by law at all, but is rather an eternal
outlaw, and in hostility with law past all atonement; both
<qex>diagonal</qex> contraries, as much allowing one another as day and
night together in one hemisphere.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

